utilities
Class wind_vector

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--utilities.wind_vector
public class wind_vector
extends java.lang.Object

Overview
This class provides a simple class to store information about a wind vector. This class stores the wind speed and direction components of a wind measurement and provides methods to calculate wind speeds at other elevations using a power wind profile.
The power law equation describing wind speed as a function of elevation is
u(z)=a z^p [a = u z^(-p)]
Note that for nuetral stability one typically assumes that p=0.25. Note that the coordinate system used in this class is the standard geometrical system. i.e. angles are measured counter clockwise from the x-axis.

Version:
1.0 (October 2001)
Author:
Tony Held
